# Gen2 source-binding portability (Message A §3).
# The Gen2 experiment binding hashes source files. To keep the working-tree
# bytes identical on every platform (Windows dev checkout vs GitHub Ubuntu
# runner), the file types that participate in binding/verification are forced
# to LF in the working tree. This is a belt; the canonical newline-normalizing
# source hash (python-source-canonical-sha256 v2) is the suspenders and remains
# required on its own — policy here is NOT sufficient by itself.
*.py   text eol=lf
*.yml  text eol=lf
*.yaml text eol=lf
*.json text eol=lf
